# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Robin Environment Variables
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# This is a pointer file. The authoritative env contracts live in the
# packages that own the runtime:
#
#   core/.env.example   Server, DB, Redis, auth, encryption, queues,
#                       LLM providers, MCP. This is what core/ validates
#                       on boot, so it is the source of truth.
#
#   wiki/.env.example   Next.js frontend variables (Robin API URL).
#
# Copy each into a sibling .env in its package and fill in values.
# Generate secrets with: openssl rand -hex 32
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
